description:
&lt;p&gt;The Hull &amp; East Riding Community Heart Failure Specialist Nurse Service is looking for a highly skilled, enthusiastic and dynamic nurse to fill a rare Band 7 vacancy within the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service provides expert support, advice, medication and clinical reviews for patients diagnosed with heart failure across Hull and the East Riding of Yorkshire.  Patient care is delivered within community based clinics and patients homes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must have significant cardiology/heart failure knowledge/experience along with enthusiasm and drive for this field of practice and a commitment to ongoing learning/development.  Candidates are required to demonstrate a high level of clinical and care management skills along with leadership and service development experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; A flexible approach to practice, excellent communication skills and the ability to work autonomously are all essential for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An ability to commute within the Organisations geographical area with access to a suitable means of transport is essential.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries are welcomed by Tracy Turner, Clinical Team Lead tracy.turner10@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
